</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="378" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1626,1975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,674,1662,1687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,1662,1687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Holotype</typeStatus>
description. Head and thorax.
</emphasis>
Structural features of head and thorax much as described above for 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,261,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,261,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">A. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[268,359,1698,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[268,359,1698,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except median length of crown slightly greater than interocular width and approximately 8/10 transocular width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1626,1975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1770,1795]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Color.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[486,570,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) mostly dark green with inconspicuous yellow or brown markings; apex of crown with yellow macula bordered by pair of brown maculae; lateral margins of crown brownish-yellow with dark brown to black lines associated with muscle impressions; coronal, frontogenal, and temporal sutures dark brown to black; mesonotum with pair of basal yellow maculae. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[995,1128,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
) mostly dark green, except apical membranous area. Face and lateral and ventral portions of thorax (
<figureCitation box="[982,1063,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) mostly yellow; labium, labrum, and legs (
<figureCitation box="[259,338,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) brownish-yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" targetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1344,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
