<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1498,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1498,1523]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[499,586,1498,1523]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, very strongly produced posteriorly; dorsoapical portion folded inwards. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[540,625,1534,1559]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, with basal third broad, narrowing gradually towards slender median third; apical third digitiform, appearing articulated with median third; in lateral view, plate not extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[825,910,1606,1631]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped but also expanded apically (and thus somewhat resembling an “I”); stalk narrow, without dorsal median keel; arms broad. Style (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly farther than apex of connective; without preapical lobe, with slight median lobe; apical portion directed ventrally; apex acute (
<figureCitation box="[812,896,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1177,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Figs. 16–17</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, elongate, gently curved dorsally, with pair of apical processes directed anterad (
<figureCitation box="[1205,1290,1750,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); dorsal area with process at anteapical portion and another one at apex, both dentiform (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1127,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1367,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) with distinct, median digitiform ventral process; basiventral portion with pair of small sclerotized projections directed to midline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1498,2027]" box="[199,400,1894,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1498,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1930,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[648,704,1931,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felixi">
<emphasis box="[648,704,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">felixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is given in honor of Dr. Márcio E. Felix (Laboratório de Biodiversidade Entomológica, Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 
<collectingRegion box="[790,960,1966,1991]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
) in recognition of his contribution to the development of Brazilian entomology and friendship.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="380" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,501,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="380">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="380">Type</typeStatus>
material. 
<typeStatus box="[383,496,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="380">Holotype</typeStatus>
:
